transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes. Hello. I was just calling to get a refill on my prescription there.

Speaker 1: Sure. Not a problem. Give me one second.

Speaker 2: All right. Robert, can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 1: Yes. 3-18-48.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you so much. I see your profile.

Speaker 1: You want to do another – actually, we have way better deals right now.

Speaker 2: So you're paying $263.95 for a quantity of 50 – just the generic Viagra.

Speaker 1: You haven't tried the new AGV, which is Pfizer's latest formula.

Speaker 2: It works better. It just kicks in quicker. It's just better.

Speaker 1: And right now you can get a quantity of 40 for $163.95.

Speaker 2: So you'd be saving $100.

Speaker 1: Okay. And if I stayed with the other form, I could get 50 for about the same price?

Speaker 2: No. You're paying $263.95 for a quantity of 50.

Speaker 1: Okay. And then the price you quoted me was what again?

Speaker 2: $163.95 for a quantity of 40.

Speaker 1: Okay. Go ahead and do that if you would, please.

Speaker 2: Okay. Yeah. Not saving $100.

Speaker 1: Are we still using your Visa ending in 7-1-0-9?

Speaker 2: Let me check. I don't think so.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I've got another – no, I've had fraud on that account. I've got another Visa here.

Speaker 1: Okay. I'm ready for the number when you are.

Speaker 2: Okay. Numbers 4147, 1802, 6987, 3028.

Speaker 1: Expiration date?

Speaker 2: 10-29.

Speaker 1: Three digits on the back.

Speaker 2: 274.

Speaker 1: All right. Perfect. That went through. They'll be shipping it out to you today.

Speaker 2: Okay. That sounds fine.

Speaker 1: Can you just send them to me like just so I can avoid the phone call and reordering and stuff?

Speaker 2: Could you send them another prescription like in 60 days or something?

Speaker 1: Sure. So a quantity of 40 actually sends you refills every three months.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: So your next one would go out April 28th of 2026.

Speaker 2: Okay. Okay.

Speaker 1: And if I wanted, I could get a refill prior to that?

Speaker 2: Yeah. Yeah. If you need a refill before that, just give us a call.

Speaker 1: Okay. Okay.

Speaker 2: All right. Perfect. You're up.

Speaker 1: We're done, okay?

Speaker 2: Yep. We're done.

Speaker 1: Okay. Well, thanks for your help now.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Okay. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
